  "text": "The use of diffuse tensor imaging (DTI) and paraspinal mapping (PM) techniques can reduce the decompression levels of lumbar spinal stenosis than conventional MRI + NE [CITATION_1] . However, with decompression levels determined by conventional MRI + NE increasing, whether the benefits of conventional MRI + (DTI or PM) will be more obvious is unknown.",
